'''Sasha Pieterse Sheaffer<!-- Instagram bio user of her verified accounts confirms her last name change ‚Äì see Talk page -->''' ({{IPAc-en|Àà|p|iÀê|t|…ôr|s|…ô}}; born February 17, 1996<ref name=sweet61>{{cite web | url=http://prettylittleliars.alloyentertainment.com/sasha-pieterse-birthday-wishes-sweet-sixteen|title=Sweet Sixteen: Happy Birthday Wishes for Pretty Little Liars Star Sasha Pieterse|publisher=[[Alloy Entertainment]]|date=March 2, 2017|archive-date=February 25, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120225045946/http://prettylittleliars.alloyentertainment.com/sasha-pieterse-birthday-wishes-sweet-sixteen/|url-status=dead}}</ref>) is an American actress and singer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.myfanbase.de/serien/interviews/?pid=9671|title=Interview with Sasha Pieterse|website=myFanbase|language=de|access-date=October 6, 2019|archive-date=October 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201019063954/https://www.myfanbase.de/serien/interviews/?pid=9671|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.thesouthafrican.com/opinion/bright-young-things-top-ten-south-african-actors-about-to-make-it-big/|title=Top Ten South African actors about to make it big|journal=The South African|first=Brett|last=Petzer|date=11 November 2013|accessdate=14 January 2023|archive-date=January 14, 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230114072025/https://www.thesouthafrican.com/opinion/bright-young-things-top-ten-south-african-actors-about-to-make-it-big/|url-status=live}}</ref> She is known for portraying [[Alison DiLaurentis]] in the [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]] series ''[[Pretty Little Liars]]'' (2010‚Äì2017), and its spin-off ''[[Pretty Little Liars: The Perfectionists]]'' (2019), for which she received global stardom and critical acclaim. 

After early recognition for her roles as Buffy Davis in ''[[Family Affair (2002 TV series) |Family Affair]]'' (2002-2003) and as Marissa Electricidad / Ice Princess in the film ''[[The Adventures of Sharkboy and Lavagirl in 3-D|The Adventures of Sharkboy and Lavagirl]]'' (2005), Pieterse played minor roles in various other films and series. She later rose to prominence with her role in ''Pretty Little Liars.'' Upon the success of ''Pretty Little Liars'', Pieterse starred in films such as [[Disney Channel]]'s ''[[Geek Charming]]'' (2011), teen comedy ''[[G.B.F. (film)|G.B.F]]'' (2013), indie film ''[[Burning Bodhi]]'' (2015), drama films ''[[Coin Heist]]'' (2017) & ''[[The Honor List]]'' (2018), and a psychological thriller film ''[[The Image of You (film)|The Image of You]]'' (2024).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/sasha-pieterse-the-perfectionists-interview|title=Sasha Pieterse on Why "The Perfectionists" Need Alison's Help|website=Teen Vogue|date=March 19, 2019|language=en|access-date=October 6, 2019|archive-date=October 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191006163223/https://www.teenvogue.com/story/sasha-pieterse-the-perfectionists-interview|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.distractify.com/p/sasha-pieterse-pregnant-bullying|title=Sasha Pieterse Stands Up to Bullies After Horrific Fat-Shaming Experience|website=Distractify|language=en|access-date=October 6, 2019|archive-date=October 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191006163225/https://www.distractify.com/p/sasha-pieterse-pregnant-bullying|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/03/the-perfectionists-sasha-pieterse-janel-parrish-interview.html|title=Sasha Pieterse and Janel Parrish Are Bringing 'Old Married Couple' Energy to The Perfectionists|website=www.vulture.com|date=March 20, 2019|access-date=October 6, 2019|archive-date=March 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190321090216/https://www.vulture.com/2019/03/the-perfectionists-sasha-pieterse-janel-parrish-interview.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

Pieterse has participated in the [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 25)|25th season]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars]]'' (2017).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hollywoodlife.com/2019/04/03/pll-the-perfectionists-alison-spoilers-sasha-pieterse-interview/|title='PLL: The Perfectionists': Sasha Pieterse Reveals Finding Nolan's Killer Is Alison's #1 Priority 'For Now'|first1=Avery|last1=Thompson|first2=Russ|last2=Weakland|date=April 3, 2019|website=HollywoodLife|language=en|access-date=October 6, 2019|archive-date=October 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191006163225/https://hollywoodlife.com/2019/04/03/pll-the-perfectionists-alison-spoilers-sasha-pieterse-interview/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thetvjunkies.com/pll-the-perfectionists-sasha-pieterse-interview/|title=PLL: The Perfectionists: Sasha Pieterse on Why This Is A New, Changed Alison|date=March 19, 2019|website=The TV Junkies|language=en-US|access-date=October 6, 2019|archive-date=October 6, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191006163225/https://www.thetvjunkies.com/pll-the-perfectionists-sasha-pieterse-interview/|url-status=dead}}</ref> In addition to acting, Pieterse has ventured into music and modeling. She served as a judge in one episode of shows ''[[Beat Bobby Flay]] and [[Sugar Rush (2018 TV series)|Sugar Rush Christmas]]'' (both 2020).

==Early life==
Pieterse was born in [[Johannesburg]], South Africa, on February 17, 1996, to Sean and Zizi.<ref name="sweet61"/><ref name=FBinfo>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/TheSashaPietersePage/info|title=TheSashaPietersePage/info|via=Facebook|access-date=March 23, 2013|archive-date=June 25, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160625134529/https://www.facebook.com/TheSashaPietersePage/info|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-09-25 |title='Dancing With The Stars' Isn't Sasha Pieterse's Only Connection To The Ballroom |url=https://www.romper.com/p/who-are-sasha-pieterses-parents-dancing-with-the-stars-isnt-her-only-connection-to-the-ballroom-2440951 |access-date=2023-07-09 |website=Romper |language=en}}</ref><!-- This Facebook account is linked to by her verified twitter account so this is a reliable source for personal info --> Pieterse's family moved to the United States in 2001, she was raised in [[Las Vegas]], before moving to [[Los Angeles]].<ref name=ABCBiography>{{cite web|title=Alison Dilaurentis by Sasha Pieterse|url=http://abcfamily.go.com/shows/pretty-little-liars/cast/alison-dilaurentis|publisher=ABC Family|access-date=March 20, 2014|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140320103903/http://abcfamily.go.com/shows/pretty-little-liars/cast/alison-dilaurentis|archive-date=March 20, 2014}}</ref> She became accustomed to a career in entertainment at an early age, as her parents were a professional [[acrobatic]] [[dance team]] who performed internationally.<ref name=ABCBiography/> Pieterse was homeschooled and graduated when she was 14 years old.<ref name=BelloMag />

