-15|website=ILuminaryWorth|language=en|archive-date=October 19, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201019021000/https://iluminaryworth.com/actress-sasha-pieterse-net-worth-pretty-little-liars-tv-series-music-relationship/|url-status=live}}</ref> Pieterse appeared in numerous magazines, including on the covers of ''BELLO''<nowiki/>'s "Young Hollywood" issue (December 2014),<ref name=BelloMag>{{cite web|last1=Elizabeth|first1=Emilie|last2=Levine|first2=Tamar|title=Sasha Pieterse By Tamar Levine & Emilie Elizabeth For Bello Mag Beauty|url=http://www.bellomag.com/sasha-pieterse-by-tamar-levine-emilie-elizabeth-for-bello-mag-beauty-december-2014/|publisher=Bello Magazine|access-date=March 21, 2015|archive-date=March 19, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150319201644/http://www.bellomag.com/sasha-pieterse-by-tamar-levine-emilie-elizabeth-for-bello-mag-beauty-december-2014/|url-status=live}}</ref> ''TeenProm'' (2015 issue),<ref>{{Cite web|last=Koch|first=Kristin|date=2014-12-23|title=PLL's Sasha Pieterse Talks Prom!|url=https://www.seventeen.com/parties/prom/sasha-pieterse-teen-prom-cover-2015|access-date=2020-12-09|website=Seventeen|language=en-US|archive-date=January 29, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150129203349/http://www.seventeen.com/parties/prom/sasha-pieterse-teen-prom-cover-2015|url-status=live}}</ref> ''[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen]]'' (August 2016), ''[[Social Life (magazine)|Social Life]]'' (August 2019).<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sasha Pieterse Magazine Cover Photos - List of magazine covers featuring Sasha Pieterse - FamousFix|url=https://www.famousfix.com/topic/sasha-pieterse/magazines|access-date=2020-10-12|website=FamousFix.com|archive-date=December 9, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151209230516/http://www.famousfix.com/topic/sasha-pieterse/magazines|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Film and television===
At the age of six, Pieterse got her start in television, co-starring in 2002 as Buffy on [[The WB]]'s [[Family Affair (2002 TV series)|remake]] of the [[CBS]] sitcom ''[[Family Affair]]''. She guest starred in the ''[[Stargate SG-1]]'' episode ‚Äú[[Grace (Stargate SG-1)|Grace]]‚Äù with [[Amanda Tapping]] as a little girl named Grace. In 2005, she appeared on an episode of ''[[House (TV series)|House]]'' titled "[[Autopsy (House)|Autopsy]]", portraying Andie, a young girl with terminal cancer. That same year, she made her film debut in ''[[The Adventures of Sharkboy and Lavagirl in 3-D]]'' as Marissa, the Ice Princess, and also appeared as Millie Rose for two episodes of the short-lived [[TNT (U.S. TV network)|TNT]] series ''[[Wanted (2005 TV series)|Wanted]]'', alongside her former ''Family Affair'' co-star, [[Gary Cole]].{{citation needed|date=May 2023}}

Pieterse appeared in the 2007 film ''[[Good Luck Chuck]]'', playing a young goth girl who places a curse on the titular character. She played the younger version of [[Sarah Michelle Gellar]]'s character in the 2007 film ''[[The Air I Breathe]]'', along with such co-stars as [[Kevin Bacon]], [[Forest Whitaker]], and [[Emile Hirsch]]. She also played a leading character in the [[Hallmark Channel|Hallmark]] original film ''Claire'', also released in 2007.{{citation needed|date=May 2023}}

Pieterse was 13 years old in late 2009, when she was cast in the [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]] [[teen drama]] television series ''[[Pretty Little Liars]]'' (2010‚Äì2017) as [[Alison DiLaurentis]], the former "[[Queen bee (sociology)|queen bee]]" of her high school clique.<ref>{{cite web |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/laura-leighton-joins-pretty-liars-92046 |title=Laura Leighton joins 'Pretty Little Liars' |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=December 6, 2009 |access-date=December 21, 2014 |archive-date=February 7, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150207075256/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/laura-leighton-joins-pretty-liars-92046 |url-status=live }}</ref> She had a regular role in the series from the first four seasons, until later became a main role in the [[Pretty Little Liars (season 5)|fifth season]], with one of the five girls. Since its debut, the series has received mixed reviews from television critics, but remained a success for Freeform, garnering a large [[fandom]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Warwick|first=Charlotte|date=2016-09-02|title=21 things you didn't know about Pretty Little Liars|url=http://www.cosmopolitan.co.uk/entertainment/a45672/pretty-little-liars-facts/|access-date=2020-10-14|website=Cosmopolitan|language=en-GB|archive-date=December 22, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222020649/http://www.cosmopolitan.co.uk/entertainment/a45672/pretty-little-liars-facts/|url-status=live}}</ref> Pieterse reprised her role as Alison, in the spin-off series titled ''[[Pretty Little Liars: The Perfectionists]]'' on [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]] in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://freeform.go.com/news/pretty-little-liars-the-perfectionists-spin-off-pilot-announced/|title=Pretty Little Liars: The Perfectionists Spin-Off Show Announced|work=Freeform|date=September 25, 2017|access-date=August 14, 2018|archive-date=March 16, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180316214329/https://freeform.go.com/news/pretty-little-liars-the-perfectionists-spin-off-pilot-announced|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=June 9, 2020|title=Pretty Little Liars Stars Celebrate 10-Year Anniversary of Show's Premiere: 'Eternally Grateful'|url=https://people.com/tv/pretty-little-liars-10-year-anniversary/|access-date=2021-12-11|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|archive-date=December 11, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211211192759/https://people.com/tv/pretty-little-liars-10-year-anniversary/|url-status=live}}</ref> On ''Pretty Little Liars: The Perfectionists'', she portrayed the grown-up version of Alison who is working as a teaching assistant at Beacon Heights University.<ref name=":0" />

Other roles Pieterse has had include a 2009 appearance in ''[[Without a Trace]]'', and a recurring role as Amanda Strazzulla, an abandoned daughter, in [[Heroes (U.S. TV series)|Heroes]]. In 2011, she appeared as Amy Loubalu in the [[Disney Channel Original Movie]] ''[[Geek Charming]]'', and also as a teenage girl in the film ''[[X-Men: First Class]]''. Later, Pieterse appeared in the film ''[[G.B.F. (film)|G.B.F.]]'' and in an episode of ''[[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|Hawaii Five-0]]'' as a terrorist pupil named Dawn Hatfield. Pieterse played Japonica Fenway, a young lady involved with cocaine, in the film ''[[Inherent Vice (film)|Inherent Vice]]'' (2014), based on the [[Inherent Vice|novel of the same name]] by [[Thomas Pynchon]].<ref name="pieterse">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2013/film/news/pretty-little-liars-sasha-pieterse-1200500298|title='Pretty Little Liars' Actress Sasha Pieterse Boards 'Inherent Vice'|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]|date=June 20, 2013|access-date=September 21, 2014|last=McNary|first=Dave|archive-date=March 14, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140314045300/http://variety.com/2013/film/news/pretty-little-liars-sasha-pieterse-1200500298/|url-status=live}}</ref> In September 2017, Pieterse was announced as one of the celebrities to compete on the [[Dancing with the Stars (American TV series) season 25|25th season]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]''. She was paired with professional dancer [[Gleb Savchenko]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/dancing-stars-season-25-celebrity-cast-frankie-muniz/story?id=49603734|title='Dancing With the Stars' season 25 celebrity cast: Frankie Muniz, Barbara Corcoran, Nick Lachey and more|work=ABC News|date=September 6, 2017|access-date=September 6, 2017|archive-date=September 6, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906144114/https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/dancing-stars-season-25-celebrity-cast-frankie-muniz/story?id=49603734|url-status=live}}</ref> They were the 4th couple eliminated, on October 16, 2017, finishing in 10th place.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.buddytv.com/articles/dancing-with-the-stars/dancing-with-the-stars-live-bl-66400.aspx|title='Dancing with the Stars' Live Blog: Disney Night with 'Moana,' Muppets and More|work=BuddyTV|date=October 16, 2017|access-date=October 16, 2017|archive-date=October 17, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171017071020/http://www.buddytv.com/articles/dancing-with-the-stars/dancing-with-the-stars-live-bl-66400.aspx|url-status=live}}</ref>

On August 16, 2021, ''[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]'' announced that Pieterse had been cast in [[Netflix]]'s film adaptation of [[Annie Barrows]]‚Äô [[The New York Times Best Seller list|New York Times bestselling]] [[book series]] ''[[Ivy + Bean]]'' alongside [[Jesse Tyler Ferguson]], [[Jane Lynch]] and [[Nia Vardalos]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|date=2021-08-16|title=Jesse Tyler Ferguson, Jane Lynch, Sasha Pieterse, Nia Vardalos & More Join Netflix Family Film Series 'Ivy & Bean'|url=https://deadline.com/2021/08/jesse-tyler-ferguson-jane-lynch-sasha-pieterse-nia-vardalos-more-join-netflix-family-film-series-ivy-bean-1234815783/|access-date=2021-11-21|website=Deadline|language=en-US|archive-date=November 11, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211111181443/https://deadline.com/2021/08/jesse-tyler-ferguson-jane-lynch-sasha-pieterse-nia-vardalos-more-join-netflix-family-film-series-ivy-bean-1234815783/|url-status=live}}</ref> In July 2023, [[Deadline Hollywood|''Deadline'']] reported that Pieterse had been cast in [[Psychological thriller|psychological thriller film]] [[The Image of You (film)|''The Image of You'']] (2024), starring in a dual roles of twin sisters of Anna and Zoe.<ref name=":2" />

=== Music ===
