Pieterse's third single, "[[I Can't Fix You]]", was released on July 12, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=I Can't Fix You - Single|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/i-cant-fix-you-single/id665967628|publisher=[[iTunes]]|access-date=March 18, 2014|archive-date=October 9, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141009160341/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/i-cant-fix-you-single/id665967628|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sasha Pieterse " I Can't Fix You" inspiration|url=http://prettylittleliars.alloyentertainment.com/sasha-pieterse-i-cant-fix-you-inspiration-715131/|access-date=March 18, 2014|publisher=Alloy Entertainment|archive-date=February 22, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222055744/http://prettylittleliars.alloyentertainment.com/sasha-pieterse-i-cant-fix-you-inspiration-715131/|url-status=live}}</ref> On December 10, 2013, she released her fourth single "No", an upbeat track about "standing strong in your convictions" and saying no when an unfaithful, lying ex-boyfriend asks for a second chance.<ref>{{cite web |author=Theo |url=http://prettylittleliars.alloyentertainment.com/sasha-pieterse-song-no-music-lyrics-100313/ |title=Sasha Pieterse Releases Country Song "No": Music & Lyrics |publisher=Alloy Entertainment |date=January 3, 2014 |access-date=March 18, 2014 |archive-date=March 3, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303233832/http://prettylittleliars.alloyentertainment.com/sasha-pieterse-song-no-music-lyrics-100313/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=No - Single - Sasha Pieterse|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/no-single/id754259345|publisher=Itunes|access-date=March 18, 2014|archive-date=September 14, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170914053412/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/no-single/id754259345|url-status=live}}</ref>

